overview: The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application
  to verify adherence to the project's acceptance criteria. The assistant
  conducted a detailed analysis of the codebase against the provided SOW and
  questionnaire specification, pinpointing several areas needing improvement.
  Following this, the assistant began implementing the high-priority items. This
  involved adding a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness, complete with critical
  safety warnings, and integrating detection and reporting for both Comorbid
  Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome.
  Additionally, a new "Resources & Next Steps" section was added to the reports,
  providing placeholder outbound links to relevant sleep and mental health
  organizations. These changes were applied across the application's data
  structures, validation logic, and user interface components, including the
  generated PDF reports.
